From: Keith Busch <keith.busch@intel.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Mar 2015 09:00:41 -0600
Subject: NVMe: Initialize device list head before starting
Git-commit: nvme-legacy 8957dd9117e9ff525d7e4ffe892f2850ce657849
Patch-Mainline: not yet
References: bnc#926056

Driver recovery requires the device's list node to have been initialized.

Fixes: https://lkml.org/lkml/2015/3/22/262

Reported-by: Steven Noonan <steven@uplinklabs.net>
Signed-off-by: Keith Busch <keith.busch@intel.com>
Acked-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/block/nvme-core.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/block/nvme-core.c b/drivers/block/nvme-core.c
index dab3916..73ce862 100644
--- a/drivers/block/nvme-core.c
+++ b/drivers/block/nvme-core.c
@@ -3050,6 +3050,7 @@ static int nvme_probe(struct pci_dev *pdev, const struct pci_device_id *id)
 	}
 	get_device(dev->device);
 
+	INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev->node);
 	INIT_WORK(&dev->probe_work, nvme_async_probe);
 	schedule_work(&dev->probe_work);
 	return 0;
